Package com.thoughtworks.robot.moves

Interface Summary
MoveFactory A MoveFactory is supposed to have all supported Move(s) so that other piece(s) of program can fetch appropriate moves (LeftMove, RightMove or StepMove or more can be added) based on moveCode (e.g.
MoveParser Interface that must be implemented by custom Move parsers which we want to user for parsing move command/string.
 

Class Summary
BaseMoveFactory A factory class for supported Move on a Plateau for a Robot.
BaseMoveParser Base class which implements MoveParser.
LeftMove This class represents a LEFT ("L") Move on Plateau.
Move Base class that represents the Movement to be performed on Plateau.
RightMove This class represents a RIGHT ("R") Move on Plateau.
StepMove This class represents a forward STEP ("M") Move on Plateau.
